STATE of North Carolina
v.
Christopher Albert TARANTINO. No. 492P05. Supreme Court of North Carolina. September 6, 2005. Joseph B. Cheshire, Raleigh, Sean P. Devereux, Asheville, for Tarantino. Michael Bonfoey, District Attorney, for State.

ORDER

Upon consideration of the petition filed by Defendant on the 6th day of September 2005 in this matter for a writ of certiorari to review the order of the Superior Court, Cherokee County, the following order was entered and is hereby certified to the Superior Court of that County:

"Dismissed Without Prejudice to Re-file in Court of Appeals, N.C.R.App. P. 21(b) by order of the Court in conference, this the 6th day of September 2005."
